did.abstract: This collection includes videotapes, photographs, posters, buttons, campaign advertisements, newsletters, and news clippings related to Cynthia Jenkins collected by Neil Tevebaugh-Kenwryck. Jenkins was a Democrat from Queens, NY.
did.physloc: This collection is located onsite in the department.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: This collection is processed by unprocessed.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Neil Tevebaugh-Kenwryck campagined for Cynthia Jenkins. He collected posters and other materials realted to her campaign.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains videotapes, photographs, posters, buttons, campaign advertisements, newsletters, and news clippings related to Cynthia Jenkins collected by Neil Tevebaugh-Kenwryck.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is unprocessed and is likely disorganized. Individual items may be difficult to find.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Neil A. Tevebaugh-Kenwryck donated his papers to the M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives in 2004.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to this collection is restricted because it is unprocessed. Portions of the collection may contain recent administrative records and/or personally identifiable information. While it is likely that portions of the collection may be viewed, access must be managed by an archivist.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The researcher assumes full responsibility for conforming with the laws of copyright. Whenever possible, the M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives will provide information about copyright owners and other restrictions, but the legal determination ultimately rests with the researcher. Requests for permission to publish material from this collection should be discussed with the Head of Special Collections and Archives.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Preferred citation for this material is as follows: Identification of specific item, series, box, folder, Tevebaugh-Kenwyruck, Neil A. Papers, 1983-1994 . M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives, University Libraries, University at Albany, State University of New York (hereafter referred to as the Tevebaugh-Kenwyruck Papers).
